str2: A primary particle; properly, indicative of affirmation or concession; usually followed by a contrasted clause with de.

parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Nominative Neuter Singular
str2: Who, which, what, that.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Little, small. Including the comparative mikroteros apparently a primary word; small (figuratively) dignity).
All, the whole, every kind of. Including all the forms of declension; apparently a primary word; all, any, every, the whole.
From speiro; something sown, i.e. Seed; by implication, offspring; specially, a remnant.
A primary particle; but, and, etc.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: (a) I cause to increase, become greater (b) I increase, grow. A prolonged form of a primary verb; to grow, i.e. Enlarge.
Large, great, in the widest sense.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
An herb, garden plant, vegetable. From lachaino; a vegetable.
And, even, also, namely.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
A tree. Probably from drus; a tree.
So that, therefore, so then, so as to. From hos and te; so too, i.e. Thus therefore.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A bird, fowl. Neuter of a derivative of petomai; a flying animal, i.e. Bird.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Perhaps from the same as oros; the sky; by extension, heaven; by implication, happiness, power, eternity; specially, the Gospel.
To come, go.
And, even, also, namely.
From kata and skenoo; to camp down, i.e. Haunt; figuratively, to remain.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Neuter 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
A young tender shoot, then: a branch; met: of descendants. From klao; a twig or bough.
